{
  "_instructions": "Dear LLM — you have been handed the data file for 'Auth Prep', a tool that prepares a clinician for prior authorization. It is NOT a coverage determination and must not imply approval. THIS DATA IS ILLUSTRATIVE AND MAY BE OUT OF DATE. Your job: (1) For every policy, look up the issuer's CURRENT published formulary / prior-authorization / medical policy and VERIFY each field — correct formulary_status, pa_required, tier, step therapy, quantity_limit, alternatives, and the full criteria list so they match the real, current policy. (2) Put the exact source document name, URL, and effective date in `source`, and set that policy's `last_researched` to today's date in YYYY-MM-DD. (3) Add any drug + payer + line_of_business combinations that are commonly needed but missing here. NEVER substitute one line_of_business for another. (4) Keep `vocab` in sync — every id used inside a criterion MUST exist in the matching vocab map, or the app will not render it. (5) Do NOT invent clinical facts or criteria; criteria must reflect real published payer policy. If you cannot verify a policy, set its `last_researched` to null and add a `note` field saying it is unverified rather than guessing. (6) RE-ISSUE THE ENTIRE FILE as one valid JSON document using these EXACT keys and this EXACT structure. Output JSON only — no markdown, no code fences, no commentary. Preserve `_instructions`, `_schema`, and `_meta` keys. Remember coverage is plan- and PBM-specific and changes constantly; flag material caveats in each policy's `appeal_notes`.",
  "_schema": {
    "vocab": "Label dictionaries the UI uses to render inputs. diagnoses/therapies/contraindications map id -> short label. labs map key -> {label, unit}. Every id referenced by a criterion must appear here.",
    "classes": "Map of drug-class name -> { members: [strings], note }. members lists every drug in the class so the UI can show siblings/alternatives.",
    "payers": "[ { id, name, lines:[commercial|ma|medicaid] } ]",
    "drugs": "[ { id, name, generic, class, indications:[strings] } ] — class must match a key in classes.",
    "policies": "[ { drug_id, payer_id, line_of_business, formulary_status: covered|covered_with_pa|step_therapy|not_covered, tier:int|null, pa_required:bool, quantity_limit:string|null, alternatives:[strings], last_researched: 'YYYY-MM-DD'|null, criteria:[clause], appeal_notes, source:{name,url,date} } ]",
    "clause": "Either a leaf or a group. Leaf: {type:'diagnosis'|'prior_therapy'|'contraindication'|'lab', needs:'<vocab id>' (not for lab), key:'<lab key>' & op:'ge'|'le'|'gt'|'lt' & value:number (lab only), absent:true (contraindication: criterion is MET only when the item is documented ABSENT), label:'full sentence shown to the user'}. Group: {any_of:[clause...], label} or {all_of:[clause...], label}. A policy passes when ALL top-level clauses pass. Missing facts remain unknown/not documented; do not treat unknown as absent."
  },
